(28, 3, '2013-03-20 18:46:35', '2013-03-20 18:46:35', 'Kleber Rodrigo de Carvalho\r\nApplication Architect\r\nMobile Phone: +55 15 9161-3362\r\nE-mail: kleber.carvalho@gmail.com\r\nWeb Site: www.KleberCarvalho.com\r\nSummary\r\nFor 17 years I have been working with Information Technology, I have practically\r\nalways used new solutions of the market, through experiences in consulting and I’m\r\ninvolved in projects for software development for many enterprises.\r\nAlso I am a technical reviewer for software development books which are translated\r\nto Portuguese.\r\nTotal Experience\r\nHardware : 14 years of experience in software development, out of which\r\n11 years and a half of experience in software development\r\nusing Java technology.\r\n: IBM System I(AS400), IBM System P AIX, System Z/Linux\r\nO. S. : UNIX, HP UX, IBM AIX, DOS, Windows, Linux, zLinux\r\nLanguages : Java, JavaScript, UML, HTML, XML\r\nJava - Threads, Collections, Advanced I/O Streams, sockets and TCP client, Java\r\nRemote Method Invocation (RMI), Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI)\r\nJ2EE - Servlet, JSP, JavaServer Faces, JavaBeans, Enterprise JavaBeans\r\nMessage Service (JMS), J2EE Connector Architecture (JCA)\r\n(EJB), Java\r\nSecurity - Java Authentication and Authorization Service (JAAS), Java Cryptography\r\nExtension (JCE), Java Secure Socket Extension (JSSE)\r\nDesktop - Swing, SWT, Java Web Start, Java Media Framework (JMF)\r\nOpen Source Frameworks - Struts, Log4J, JUnit (Unit Test), Cactus, Hibernate\r\nAspect-Oriented Programming (AOP) - AspectJ, JBoss AOP, AspectWerkz\r\nTools - Ant, XDoclet, Middlegen, AndroMDA\r\nXML - XSLT, XPATH, Apache Digester\r\nDesign Patterns - Java Design Patterns ( GOF - Classic), JEE Design Patterns (Sun)\r\nOthers - JDBC, Java Data Objects (JDO), JavaMail\r\nDatabase\r\n: IBM DB2 and DB2/AS400, Oracle DB, Microsoft SQL Server,\r\nMySql, PostGreSQL, Sybase, HSQLDB and Derby.\r\nSignificant Project\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 1 of 6\r\nProject Name : w3 Web solutions\r\nClient : IBM\r\nDuration : 4 years and 8 moth\r\nRole : Application Architect\r\nEnvironment : O.S.: AIX, Linux, zLinux\r\nDatabase: DB2\r\nLanguage: Java, XML\r\nTools: Websphere AS, Websphere MQ, OminiFind Enterprise Edition\r\nStart date : 02/15/2007\r\nEnd date : to date\r\nDescription :\r\nI’m an Application Architect to provide Life Cycle Management support for w3\r\nBluepages and w3 Search. I take ownership of any/all problems and works with SDC\r\n(Service Delivery Center), analyzing requirements with customers, help customers in\r\nmaking decisions, Application Development and providing technical expertise\r\nmanaging activities in development life cycle , working with Business teams and\r\nprovide technical leadership to resolve issues and drive production issue to closure.\r\nw3 BluePages is a very highly visible application. The environment is high pace,\r\nchallenging and complex. Bluepages is a IBM business-oriented social networking\r\nsite, mainly used for professional networking. The main purpose of the Bluepages is\r\nto allow registered IBM''s employee to maintain a list of contact details of people\r\nthey know and trust in business. Bluepages is Java Enterprise (JEE) application\r\naccessing many sources of data including LDAP, DB2, and XML pages searched by\r\nthe Omnifind search engine. Bluepages has also been packaged as an illustrative\r\nbusiness application bundled with WebSphere Application Server for Linux.\r\nW3 Search is an enterprise search system provides extensive capabilities for\r\nsearching any number of structured and unstructured data sources with a single\r\nquery. Fast query response times and a consolidated, ranked result set that is based\r\non extensive text analysis enable customers to not just locate documents of\r\ninterest, but extract meaning from document content.\r\nThe enterprise search components, which are installed with OmniFind Enterprise\r\nEdition, collect information from throughout your enterprise. By entering a query in\r\na Web browser, you can search local and remote databases, collaboration systems,\r\ncontent management systems, file systems, and internal and external Web sites at\r\nthe same time.\r\nSignificant Project\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 2 of 6\r\nProject Name : rPOS – Circuit City\r\nReplacement Point of Sale\r\nClient : IBM\r\nDuration : 8 Moths\r\nRole : Java Developer\r\nEnvironment : O.S.: AIX\r\nDatabase: DB2\r\nLanguage: Java, XML\r\nTools: Websphere AS, Websphere MQ, Webphere Broker\r\nStart date : 06/01/2006\r\nEnd date : 02/15/2007\r\nDescription :\r\nrPOS project is a new point of sale’s system of Circuit City. rPOs is huge system\r\ndivided in many components.\r\nI worked developing/support of two components:\r\nDTS Upload - The Data Transformation Services (DTS) are the processes that extract\r\noperational data from the rPOS repositories and feed the Legacy Applications.\r\nEnterprise Service Bus (ESB) - The enterprise service bus (ESB) is an architectural\r\npattern that offers a comprehensive, flexible and consistent approach to integration.\r\nThe ESB pattern is founded on and unifies message oriented, event driven and\r\nservice oriented approaches to integration. It is an integral part of a services\r\noriented architecture (SOA).\r\nESB component inside of rPOS project provides the integration (routing, mediation,\r\ntransformation and data enrichment) including virtualization and loose coupling\r\nbetween the following various components. In ESB component I worked with two\r\nkind of adapters. Adapter for synchronous services I used Http, Web Service and MQ.\r\nAdapter for asynchronous services I used MQ Input/ Output nodes.\r\nSignificant Project\r\nProject Name : IDR – Integrated Developer Relations\r\nPDI - DW – Partner Data Integration - Data Warehouse\r\nClient : IBM\r\nDuration : 8 Months\r\nRole : Java Developer\r\nEnvironment : O.S.: AIX\r\nDatabase: DB2\r\nLanguage: Java, XML\r\nStart date : 07/01/2005\r\nEnd date : 06/30/2006\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 3 of 6\r\nDescription\r\n:\r\nIDR DW project is an effort to integrate many Databases to create a Data Warehouse\r\nwhere it is a logical collection of information gathered from many different\r\noperational databases used to create business intelligence that supports business\r\nanalysis activities and decision making tasks, a record of an enterprise''s past\r\ntransactional and operational information, stored in a database designed to favour\r\nefficient data analysis and reporting.\r\nI worked with Java (batch Java application) and XML with Castor framework where\r\nCastor is an Open Source data binding framework for Java. It''s the shortest path\r\nbetween Java objects, XML documents and relational tables. Castor provides Java-to-\r\nXML binding and Java-to-SQL persistence.\r\nDeveloping programs using Java and Castor framework was built a solution to\r\nintegrated database with assistance Websphere MQ Series.\r\nIn the KT(Knowledge Transfer) phase I went in IBM Austin to work during 4 weeks\r\ntogether with my team in USA.\r\nResponsibilities :\r\nDesign, document, code and unit test as assigned\r\nAssist the Team Lead in defect prevention activities and actively participate in\r\nprocess improvements as defined in the process change management\r\ndocumentation\r\nParticipate as requested in quantitative process management, software quality\r\nmanagement, defect prevention, identifying, analyzing, and identifying the causes\r\nof defects. Work with the team lead to correct problems.\r\nSignificant Project\r\nProject Name : Contracts OnLine (COL) Release 1 (R1)\r\nClient : IBM\r\nDuration : 11 Weeks\r\nRole : Java Developer\r\nEnvironment : O.S.: AIX\r\nDatabase: DB2\r\nLanguage: Java, JavaScript, UML\r\nApplication Server: IBM Websphere AS\r\nStart date : 04/18/2005\r\nEnd date : 06/30/2005\r\nDescription :\r\nThe Contracts OnLine (COL) Release 1 (R1) project was an effort to move the On\r\nDemand Electronic Contract System (ODECS) from its current IBM Research Pilot\r\nform to a production ibm.com deployment on the Application Hosting Environment\r\n(AHE).\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 4 of 6\r\nResponsibilities :\r\nDesign, document, code and unit test as assigned\r\nContribute to the team in general on such things as discovery of changes in\r\nstandards, methods, task tracking (especially in their specialty: Notes, MQ Series,\r\nWeb, etc.)\r\nParticipate as requested in quantitative process management, software quality\r\nmanagement, defect prevention, identifying, analyzing, and identifying the causes\r\nof defects. Work with the Project Manager and team lead to correct problems.\r\nAssist the Project Manager and Team Lead in defect prevention activities and\r\nactively participate in process improvements as defined in the process change\r\nmanagement documentation\r\nSignificant Project\r\nProject Name : Several Projects in Goodyear\r\nClient : Goodyear\r\nDuration : 2 years and half\r\nRole : Java Programmer Analyst, Java Architect\r\nEnvironment : O.S.: Linux, Windows, 0S 400, AIX\r\nDatabase: Oracle. Sybase, SQL Server, DB2\r\nLanguage: Java, JavaScript, UML, XML\r\nApplication Server: Sun One AS, IBM Websphere AS, Tomcat, JBoss\r\nAS\r\nStart date : 01/02/2003\r\nEnd date : 04/16/2005\r\nDescription :\r\nTo integrate ERP JDEdwards in AS/400 with others legacy systems and make\r\navailable some modules in web (World Wide Web).\r\nI''ve been working with JTOpen framework which is an open source project supported\r\nby IBM. I developed some functionalities, for instance, translating EBCDIC file to\r\nASCII and vice-versa. One of the interfaces run inside OS/400 with thread pool using\r\nplain Java, which received message from IBM server MQSeries. This system also is\r\nintegrated with Lotus Notes application.\r\nResponsibilities :\r\nDesign component level solutions from system requirements.\r\nDevelop software solutions both from ''scratch'' and within existing architectures.\r\nCommunicate persuasively (verbal and written) with clients to provide quality\r\nsoftware solutions.\r\nTeam lead and mentor junior developers in technical and consulting skills.\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 5 of 6\r\nDocument both potential and provided solutions.\r\nReview and test software components for quality and performance.\r\nWork with architects and clients for development, testing and deployment strategies\r\nSignificant Project\r\nProject Name : Integrate all Web Systems with ERP SAP.\r\nClient : Roche healthcare company\r\nDuration : 6 month\r\nRole : Java Programmer Analyst\r\nEnvironment : O.S: Windows\r\nDatabase: Oracle, DB2\r\nLanguage: Java, JavaScript, UML, XML\r\nApplication Server: Jrun AS\r\nStart date : 06/03/2002\r\nEnd date : 12/30/2002\r\nDescription : To Integrate some modules of SAP (Enterprise Portal, Supply Chain,\r\nManagement, E-Procurement, Business Intelligence, Financial) and make available\r\ninformation on real time in web (World Wide Web).\r\nI''ve been working with SAP Java Connector (Jco) which is a middleware library\r\nallowing Java access SAP functions by RFC (Remote Function Call).\r\nResponsibilities :\r\nDesign component level solutions from system requirements.\r\nDevelop software solutions both from ''scratch'' and within existing architectures.\r\nCommunicate persuasively (verbal and written) with clients to provide quality\r\nsoftware solutions.\r\nMentor junior developers in technical and consulting skills.\r\nDocument both potential and provided solutions.\r\nReview and test software components for quality and performance.\r\nWork with architects and clients for development, testing and deployment\r\nstrategies.\r\nSignificant Project\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 6 of 6\r\nProject Name : Cartão de Fidelidade Dotz (Dotz Fidelity Card)\r\nClient : Dotz.com.br\r\nDuration : 6 months\r\nRole : J2EE Analyst/Developer\r\nEnvironment : O.S.: Linux and Windows\r\nDatabase: Oracle. Sybase, SQL Server, DB2\r\nLanguage: Java, JavaScript, UML, XML\r\nApplication Server: Sun One AS, IBM Websphere AS, Tomcat\r\nStart date : 02/02/2002\r\nEnd date : 06/02/2002\r\nDescription : It was a fidelity e-commerce system. The more people buy a product,\r\nthe more “Dotz” currency they accumulate for exchanging by new products.\r\nResponsibilities :\r\nSystem Requirement Analyst\r\nSystem architecture designer using the CASE Together Tool.\r\nDatabase designer using ErWin tool for database modelling.\r\nSystem Developer for Several Modules\r\nSignificant Project\r\nProject Name : Vesper Telecommunication Web Site Maintenance\r\nClient : Vesper Telecommunications\r\nDuration : 1 year\r\nRole : J2EE Analyst/Developer\r\nEnvironment : O.S.: Linux\r\nDatabase: Oracle\r\nLanguage: Java, JavaScript, UML\r\nApplication Server: JServe Conector with Apache Web Server\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 7 of 6\r\nStart date : 02/01/2001\r\nEnd date : 02/01/2002\r\nDescription : The project was the main Web Site of the Vesper\r\nTelecommunications. In this Web site were made all the lyfe-cycle control from a\r\npurchase of new telephone line, until a daily assistance to the user of the telephone\r\nline.\r\nResponsibilities :\r\nSpecify new functionalities according to the clients'' needs.\r\nDesign new functionalities using UML with RUP in the CASE Rational Rose Tool.\r\nDevelop new functionalities using Java (Servlets and JSP)\r\nActed as an Assistant in the Database project using the ErWin Tool, for modelling\r\nnew functionalities to the Database.\r\nSignificant Project\r\nI have studied in my free time open source projects and software methodology\r\nwhich I have interest such as:\r\nFrameworks:\r\n- Spring framework\r\n- Hibernate\r\nDatabase:\r\n- HSQLDB\r\n- Apache Derby\r\nApplication Server\r\n- Apache Geronimo\r\n- Glassfish AS\r\nSoftware Methodology\r\n- Extreme Program\r\n- Scrum\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 8 of 6\r\nI''m a technical reviewer for software development books which are translated to\r\nPortuguese, such as:\r\n- Struts in Action\r\n- Linux Power Tools,\r\n- Linux Kernel Development\r\n- JavaServer Faces Programming\r\n- EJB Cookbook\r\n- How Tomcat works\r\n- Hibernate in Action\r\n- The UML Reference Manual\r\n- J2EE Tutorial 1.4\r\n- Core Servlets &amp; JavaServer Pages (2nd Edition)\r\n- Building Web Services with Java: Making Sense of XML, SOAP, WSDL, and UDDI\r\n(2nd Edition)\r\n- The Essential Guide to HTML5: Using Games to learn HTML5\r\n- Pro Android Web Apps Develop for Android Using HTML5, CSS3 &amp; JavaScript\r\n- iOS 4 in Action: Examples and Solutions for iPhone &amp; iPad\r\nEducation\r\nBachelor :\r\nGraduated in Computer Science, by UNIMEP (Universidade Metodista de Piracicaba,\r\nPiracicaba Methodist University), in the year 2000.\r\nLato Sensu post-graduation with the title of " Java and Java Enterprise Edition\r\nArchitecture Specialist ", by FIAP (Faculdade de Informática e Administração\r\nPaulista, Computer and Administration Faculty from São Paulo), in the year 2002.\r\nMBA (Master Business Administration) with the title of “High Availability in Enterprise\r\nArchitecture”, by FIAP (Faculdade de Informática e Administração Paulista, Computer\r\nand Administration Faculty from São Paulo), in the year 2010.\r\nOther Experiences\r\n01/2007 – to date\r\nIBM Java Center of Competence\r\nDescription: Java Advisor\r\nJava CoC is a Brazilian community, whose members are interested in Java and Web\r\nrelated technologies. Its mains goal is to improve the technical skills ans spread Java\r\nTechnology knowledge.\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 9 of 6\r\n01/2007 – to date\r\nIBM Academic Initiative Brazil Ambassador\r\nDescription: Academic Ambassador\r\nVolunter work to create a maintain a link between IBM and Universities, spreading\r\nIBM technology in the Academic environment.\r\nLanguage Proficiency\r\nAbility Expectations\r\n English: Fluent  Spanish: Advanced Fluent Ability for overseas assignment\r\n French: Basic Advanced Able to take an overseas business trip\r\nunaccompanied\r\nIntermediate Read and Write ability with limited verbal skill\r\n(able to take an overseas business trip with an\r\nassistant).\r\nBasic Able to communicate with people from other\r\ncountries at a minimum level\r\nOther Information\r\nAward :\r\nCertification :\r\nInternational Experience :\r\n Moths: 1\r\n Location: United States - IBM Austin, Texas\r\n Weeks: 6\r\n Location: United States – Circuit City Richmond, Virginia\r\n Moths: 2\r\n Location: United States – Circuit City Richmond, Virginia\r\nTravel Information\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 10 of 6\r\nAvailability for Travel (1 to 4 months):\r\nYes\r\nNo\r\nAvailability to Move to:\r\n• Hortolandia Yes No\r\n• São Paulo Yes No\r\n• Rio de Janeiro Yes No\r\nPassport Expiration Date: 07/01/2010\r\n•\r\nPassport VISA B1/B2:\r\nYes\r\nNo\r\n_____________________________________________________________\r\nAvailable to start the work in:\r\nI’ll be available a month after I’m approved to new project.\r\nLast Rev: 5/25/2012\r\nPage 11 of 6', 'Kleber Rodrigo de Carvalho', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '24-revision-3', '', '', '2013-03-20 18:46:35', '2013-03-20 18:46:35', '', 24, 'http://localhost/controle-cv/?p=28', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(30, 3, '2013-03-20 19:49:16', '2013-03-20 19:49:16', '<h3><b>Reifran Miler Oliveira</b></h3>\r\n<pre>Líder de Projetos – cliente Claro Telecomunicações - SysMap Solutions\r\n\r\n<b>APRESENTAÇÃO PESSOAL</b>\r\n\r\nFormado pela Universidade Católica de Minas Gerais (PUC) em 2004, iniciei \r\nminhas atividades profissionais no ano de 2003 como desenvolvedor de \r\nsistemas e hoje atuo como consultor tecnológico e gestor de projetos. Tive \r\na oportunidade de trabalhar em sistemas para empresas de grande porte, das \r\nquais destaco: Coca Cola Brasil, Gerdau Açominas, Arcelor Mittal, Telemar / \r\nOi, Telemig Celular, Vivo e Claro. Atualmente trabalho gerente de negócio e projetos para líder para Prefeitura Municipal de São Paulo.\r\n\r\n<b>RESUMO DAS QUALIFICAÇÕES</b>\r\n\r\n• Facilidade de relacionamento, motivação de equipe, gestão de fornecedores \r\ne gestão de conflitos internos são pontos fortes em minha carreira;\r\n\r\n• Conhecedor de comércio eletrônico, web marketing e área de processos \r\n(RUP, PMBOOK, CMMI, MSF);\r\n\r\n• Atuei como gerente de projetos na restruturação do canal de vendas on \r\nline da Telemig Celular, proporcionando um aumento superior a 200% nas \r\nvendas logo após seu lançamento;\r\n• Gerenciei o projeto de portabilidade numérica para sua disponibilização \r\nem meio on line,\r\npossibilitando aumento da carteira de clientes da operadora Telemig \r\nCelular, além de trazer\r\nagilidade e comodidade aos clientes;\r\n\r\n• Participante ativo do processo de integração entre as operadoras Telemig \r\nCelular e Vivo,\r\nrealizando levantamento de gaps entre os sistemas, definição arquitetural \r\nde integração e gestão do projeto de integração SAP para área web de vendas;\r\n\r\n• Atuante junto às áreas de negócio, procurando demonstrar como a T.I. pode \r\ntrazer grande valor ao negócio, otimizando processos, agilizando a \r\nidentificação de falhas, melhorando a experiência dos usuários internos e \r\nexternos em relação a navegação dos sistemas.\r\n\r\n<b>ESPECIALIDADES</b>\r\n\r\nGestão de Projetos, Projetos de Comércio Eletrônico (e-commerce), \r\nDocumentação Padrão UML, Gestão de Equipes, Gestão de Fornecedores, \r\nLevantamento Funcional\r\n\r\n<b>EXPERIÊNIA PROFISSIONAL</b>\r\n\r\nLíder de Projeto (Claro Telecomunicações) na SysMap Solutions\r\nDezembro 2009 – Atual (9 meses)\r\n\r\nResponsável pela frente de legados do projeto CPC Claro Telecomunicações. A \r\nfrente de legados tem como objetivo garantir que os sistemas da Claro \r\nsofram o menor impacto possível com a implantação do projeto. Definir as \r\nestratégias de migração de dados com foco no impacto dos sistemas legados e \r\ngerenciar requisitos, desenvolvimento, testes e implantação dos ajustes \r\nnecessários aos legados.\r\n\r\nGestor de Canais Eletrônicos na Vivo\r\nDezembro 2007 - Dezembro 2009 (2 anos 1 mês)\r\n\r\nResponsável pela manutenção e evolução do canal de comércio eletrônico da \r\nVivo MG. Atuando na gestão de parceiros garantindo assim o atendimento das \r\nnecessidades do negócio da corporação.\r\n\r\nGerente de Projetos na SysMap Solutions\r\nJulho 2007 - Dezembro 2007 (6 meses)\r\n\r\nResponsável pela gestão de projetos, em particular a restruturação do canal \r\nde vendas on line da organização Telemig Celular - atual Vivo MG.\r\n\r\nAnalista Projetista na Attps Informática S/A\r\nJulho 2005 - Julho 2007 (2 anos 1 mês)\r\n\r\nResponsável pelos projetos de software, atendendo as necessidades dos \r\nclientes. Gestão de equipe de desenvolvimento, análise de requisitos e \r\nrevisão das planilhas de pontos de função.\r\n\r\nAnalista D.W. na CPM Braxis\r\nJulho 2005 – Agosto 2005 (2 meses)\r\n\r\nResponsável pelo processo ETL para banco da dados Tera Data e Sql Server \r\n2000 (DTS),\r\nconstrução de cubos utilizando ferramenta Microsoft Analysis Service com \r\nFront-End Microsoft\r\nExcel, gerando relatórios para a área financeira da organização Telemar / \r\nOi.\r\n\r\nAnalista de Sistemas na Cadsoft – Softwares Academicos\r\nJulho 2003 - Julho 2005 (2 anos 1 mês)\r\n\r\nAnalista responsável pelos canais educacionais para estudantes e \r\nprofessores das universidades clientes.\r\n\r\nDesenvolvedor na Prodabel (Processamento de Dados de Belo Horizonte)\r\nFevereiro  2003 - Julho 2003 (6 meses)\r\n\r\nDesenvolvimento de sistema para o departamento de saúde utilizando \r\nferramenta Delphi e Sql\r\nServer\r\n\r\n<b>EDUCAÇÃO</b>\r\n\r\nIbmec Business School\r\nGestão de Pessoas, 2009 – 2010\r\n\r\nPontifícia Universidade Católica de Minas Gerais\r\nBacharelado, Ciência da Computação, Redes Neurais Artificiais, Sistemas de \r\nInformação, Usabilidade Homem Máquina, 2000 – 2004\r\n\r\nEnglish Express / Mai Escola de Idiomas / Liberty School \r\nNível: Intermediário – 2 anos e 6 meses</pre>', 'Reifran Miler Oliveira', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'reifran-miler-oliveira', '', '', '2013-03-20 19:49:16', '2013-03-20 19:49:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost/controle-cv/?p=30', 0, 'post', '', 6),
(34, 1, '2013-03-22 20:55:14', '2013-03-22 20:55:14', '<pre>Objetivo: Analista Desenvolvedor\r\n\r\nResumo Profissional\r\nMais de doze anos de experiência em desenvolvimento de sistemas com sólidos \r\nconhecimentos em Asp.Net, C#, Html, Xml, Ajax, Javascript, SQL Server 2008, \r\nprogramação orientada o objeto.\r\n\r\nFormação Acadêmica\r\nTecnologia em Processamento de Dados \r\nFATEC-AM (Faculdade de Tecnologia de Americana) -\r\n\r\nIdiomas\r\nInglês fluente\r\nI lived and studied for a year at high school in Mill Spring North Carolina, \r\nUSA as AFS exchange student.\r\n\r\nExperiência Profissional\r\n\r\nBMW Financeira (WA Consultoria)\r\nInício em 01/10/2012  \r\nTrabalhou no  projeto Dealer Front End – simulador de financiamento para \r\nconcessionárias BMW.  ASP. NET C#, JQuery,javaScript, Ajax e SQL2008 .\r\n\r\nFOXCONN  (WA Consultoria)\r\nPeríodo de 01/07/2011 a 28/09/2012\r\nTrabalhou no projeto da intranet da FOXCONN, ASP. NET C# e \r\nSQL2008/Oracle.JQuery e integração SAP.\r\n\r\nWA Consultoria – Fábrica Sofware\r\nInício em 26/07/2010 a 30/06/2012\r\nTrabalhou no desenvolvimento de projetos para clientes como \r\nDeloitte,Empax,KPMG, Banco ABC , ASP. NET C# e SQL2005/Oracle.JQuery\r\n\r\nDatora Telecomunicações\r\nImplantou Sistema de tarifação de chamadas para faturamento.  Linguagens ASP. \r\nNET C# ,JavaScript, programação orientada a objeto, programação em camadas, \r\nbando de dados SQL2000  (stored procedures, views)\r\nPeríodo de 01/01/2010 a 16/07/2010\r\nConsultoria : Resolve Consultec\r\n\r\nMutual Seguros\r\nImplantou aplicativo para controle de compras, requisições e estoque de \r\nsuprimentos. Linguagens ASP. NET C# , JavaScript, programação orientada a \r\nobjeto, programação em camadas, banco de dados SQL2005  (stored procedures, \r\nviews)\r\nPeríodo de 01/01/2010 a 16/07/2010\r\nConsultoria : Resolve Consultec\r\n\r\nEasyTone Telecomunicações\r\nDesenvolveu aplicativo para gestão empresarial, compras, vendas, estoque, \r\nfinanceiro, tarifação de chamadas e emissão de Nota Fiscal Eletrônica modelo \r\n21 e modelo 55  Linguagens ASP. NET C# , JavaScript, AJAX.NET, programação \r\norientada a objeto, programação em camadas, banco de dados SQL2000  (stored \r\nprocedures, views), comunicação com webservice (XML)\r\nPeríodo de 19/11/2007 a 31/12/2009\r\nConsultoria : Resolve Consultec\r\n\r\nTellus Telecomunicações \r\nDesenvolveu sistema de controle de pagamentos de Benefícios. C# para Desktop \r\ne programação orientada a objeto, programação em camadas, bando de dados \r\nSQL2000  (stored procedures, views),\r\nPeríodo de 19/11/2007 a 31/07/2008 \r\nConsultoria : Resolve Consultec\r\n\r\n“A Hebraica” São Paulo \r\nImplantou aplicativo para controle de compras, requisições e estoque de \r\nsuprimentos. E-procurement. ASP 2.0 e SQL2000. \r\nDesenvolveu Aplicativo para controle de acesso com identificação biométrica.  \r\nC# para WEB/Desktop e SQL2000\r\nPeríodo de 15/07/2002 a 16/11/2007\r\nConsultoria : Resolve Consultec\r\n\r\nAGF Allianz Seguros\r\nTrabalhou no desenvolvimento de aplicativo para controle de compras, \r\nrequisições e estoque de suprimentos.  Delphi 5 e SQL2000\r\nPeríodo de 26/12/2001 a 12/07/2002\r\nConsultoria : VM Consultoria de Sistemas AS\r\n\r\nHewlett-Packard\r\nTrabalhou no desenvolvimento de aplicativo para cotação de máquinas e \r\nservidores. Asp 2.0 SQL2000. Ferramenta WorkFlow.\r\nPeríodo de 26/03/2001 a 27/11/2001\r\nConsultoria : Officeware automação Ltda.\r\n\r\nMobitel  Telecomunicações  (Atual Dedic) \r\nTrabalhou no desenvolvimento de aplicativo para  atendimento de chamadas, \r\nativo e receptivo. Delphi 4 e SQL 7.0\r\nPeríodo de 06/06/2000 a 13/03/2001 – CLT\r\n\r\nCursos\r\n• Programming a Microsoft SQL Server 2000 Database\r\n• Programming with Microsoft Visual Basic .NET \r\n• Programming ADO.NET \r\n• Building COM+ Applications Using Microsoft .NET Enterprise Services \r\n• Developing XML Web Services Using Microsoft ASP.NET\r\n• Developing Microsoft ASP.NET Web Applications Using Visual Studio .NET</pre>', 'Marcos Antonio Carraro', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'marcos-antonio-carraro', '', '', '2013-03-22 20:55:14', '2013-03-22 20:55:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/controle-cv/?p=34', 0, 'post', '', 0),
